2.0数据准备¶

In [1]:
import numpy as np
from sklearn import datasets
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# 1.  [1]
iris = datasets.load_iris()
X = iris.data[:, [1, 3]]
y = iris.target

# 2.  (30%) [3, 4]
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=1, stratify=y)

# 3. SVMKNN [5, 6]
sc = StandardScaler()
sc.fit(X_train)
X_train_std = sc.transform(X_train)
X_test_std = sc.transform(X_test)

#  [2, 7]
from matplotlib.colors import ListedColormap
def plot_decision_regions(X, y, classifier, test_idx=None, resolution=0.02):
    markers = ('o', 's', '^', 'v', '<')
    colors = ('red', 'blue', 'lightgreen', 'gray', 'cyan')
    cmap = ListedColormap(colors[:len(np.unique(y))])
    x1_min, x1_max = X[:, 0].min() - 1, X[:, 0].max() + 1
    x2_min, x2_max = X[:, 1].min() - 1, X[:, 1].max() + 1
    xx1, xx2 = np.meshgrid(np.arange(x1_min, x1_max, resolution),
                           np.arange(x2_min, x2_max, resolution))
    lab = classifier.predict(np.array([xx1.ravel(), xx2.ravel()]).T)
    lab = lab.reshape(xx1.shape)
    plt.contourf(xx1, xx2, lab, alpha=0.3, cmap=cmap)
    for idx, cl in enumerate(np.unique(y)):
        plt.scatter(x=X[y == cl, 0], y=X[y == cl, 1], alpha=0.8, c=colors[idx],
                    marker=markers[idx], label=f'Class {cl}', edgecolor='black')
    if test_idx:
        X_test, y_test = X[test_idx, :], y[test_idx]
        plt.scatter(X_test[:, 0], X_test[:, 1], c='none', edgecolor='black', 
                    alpha=1.0, linewidth=1, marker='o', s=100, label='Test set')

X_combined_std = np.vstack((X_train_std, X_test_std))
y_combined = np.hstack((y_train, y_test))

In [2]:
from sklearn.linear_model import Perceptron
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix
import numpy as np

#  [8]
# eta0=0.1()random_state=1()
ppn = Perceptron(eta0=0.1, random_state=1)
ppn.fit(X_train_std, y_train)

#  [8, 10]
y_pred = ppn.predict(X_test_std)
acc = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
print(f': {acc:.3f}')
print(f'\n:\n{classification_report(y_test, y_pred, target_names=iris.target_names)}')

# 
conf_matrix = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
print(f':\n{conf_matrix}')

#  [7]
plot_decision_regions(X_combined_std, y_combined, classifier=ppn, test_idx=range(105, 150))
plt.title('Perceptron')
plt.show()

from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix

#  OvR  [14]
# C=100.0(C)solver='lbfgs'()multi_class='ovr'()
lr = LogisticRegression(C=100.0, solver='lbfgs', multi_class='ovr', max_iter=1000)
lr.fit(X_train_std, y_train)

#  [15]
prob = lr.predict_proba(X_test_std[:3, :])
print(f'Probabilities of first 3 samples:\n{prob}\n')

# 
y_pred_lr = lr.predict(X_test_std)
acc_lr = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_lr)
print(f': {acc_lr:.3f}')
print(f'\n:\n{classification_report(y_test, y_pred_lr, target_names=iris.target_names)}')

# 
conf_matrix_lr = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_lr)
print(f':\n{conf_matrix_lr}')

#  [14]
plot_decision_regions(X_combined_std, y_combined, classifier=lr, test_idx=range(105, 150))
plt.title('Logistic Regression (C=100)')
plt.show()

2.3支持向量机和核方法¶

In [4]:
from sklearn.svm import SVC
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix

# 1.  SVM [19]
# kernel='linear'()C=1.0()random_state=1()
svm_linear = SVC(kernel='linear', C=1.0, random_state=1)
svm_linear.fit(X_train_std, y_train)

y_pred_linear = svm_linear.predict(X_test_std)
acc_linear = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_linear)
print(f'SVM: {acc_linear:.3f}')
print(f': {len(svm_linear.support_vectors_)}\n')

# 2.  SVM ( RBF ) [18, 20]
# gamma ""gamma  [20, 21]
# kernel='rbf'(RBF)gamma=0.2()C=1.0()
svm_rbf = SVC(kernel='rbf', random_state=1, gamma=0.2, C=1.0)
svm_rbf.fit(X_train_std, y_train)

y_pred_rbf = svm_rbf.predict(X_test_std)
acc_rbf = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_rbf)
print(f'RBF-SVM: {acc_rbf:.3f}')
print(f': {len(svm_rbf.support_vectors_)}')
print(f'\nRBF-SVM:\n{classification_report(y_test, y_pred_rbf, target_names=iris.target_names)}')

# 
conf_matrix_rbf = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_rbf)
print(f':\n{conf_matrix_rbf}')

#  SVM  [20]
plot_decision_regions(X_combined_std, y_combined, classifier=svm_rbf, test_idx=range(105, 150))
plt.title('Kernel SVM (RBF, gamma=0.2)')
plt.show()

from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn import tree
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix

# 4 [23]
# criterion='gini'()max_depth=4()
tree_model = DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion='gini', max_depth=4, random_state=1)
tree_model.fit(X_train, y_train) # 

# 
y_pred_tree = tree_model.predict(X_test)
acc_tree = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_tree)
print(f': {acc_tree:.3f}')
print(f': {tree_model.get_depth()}')
print(f': {tree_model.get_n_leaves()}')
print(f'\n:\n{classification_report(y_test, y_pred_tree, target_names=iris.target_names)}')

# 
conf_matrix_tree = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_tree)
print(f':\n{conf_matrix_tree}')

# 
feature_importance = tree_model.feature_importances_
print(f'\n:')
print(f'  Petal Length: {feature_importance[0]:.3f}')
print(f'  Petal Width:  {feature_importance[1]:.3f}')

#  [24]
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 7))
tree.plot_tree(tree_model, filled=True, 
               feature_names=['Petal length', 'Petal width'])
plt.show()

#  [23]
X_combined_orig = np.vstack((X_train, X_test))
plot_decision_regions(X_combined_orig, y_combined, classifier=tree_model, test_idx=range(105, 150))
plt.title('Decision Tree')
plt.show()

2.6 模型对比与分析¶

In [7]:
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')

# matplotlib
plt.rcParams['font.sans-serif'] = ['SimHei']  # 
plt.rcParams['axes.unicode_minus'] = False  # 

# 
models_performance = {
    '': {
        '': accuracy_score(y_test, ppn.predict(X_test_std)),
        '': [],
        '': [],
        '': 'eta0=0.1'
    },
    '': {
        '': accuracy_score(y_test, lr.predict(X_test_std)),
        '': [],
        '': [],
        '': 'C=100.0'
    },
    'SVM': {
        '': accuracy_score(y_test, svm_linear.predict(X_test_std)),
        '': [],
        '': [],
        '': 'kernel=linear, C=1.0'
    },
    'RBF-SVM': {
        '': accuracy_score(y_test, svm_rbf.predict(X_test_std)),
        '': [],
        '': [],
        '': 'kernel=rbf, gamma=0.2, C=1.0'
    },
    '': {
        '': accuracy_score(y_test, tree_model.predict(X_test)),
        '': [],
        '': [],
        '': 'max_depth=4'
    },
    'KNN(k=5)': {
        '': accuracy_score(y_test, knn.predict(X_test_std)),
        '': [],
        '': [],
        '': 'n_neighbors=5'
    }
}

# 
accuracies = {name: info[''] for name, info in models_performance.items()}

# 
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
models = list(accuracies.keys())
accs = list(accuracies.values())
colors = ['#FF6B6B', '#4ECDC4', "#52B0C5", '#96CEB4', '#FFEAA7', '#DDA0DD']

bars = plt.bar(models, accs, color=colors, edgecolor='black', linewidth=1.5)
plt.ylabel('', fontsize=12)
plt.xlabel('', fontsize=12)
plt.title('', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
plt.ylim([0.85, 1.0])

# 
for bar, acc in zip(bars, accs):
    height = bar.get_height()
    plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width()/2., height,
             f'{acc:.3f}', ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10)

plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.3)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# 
print("=" * 80)
print("")
print("=" * 80)
summary_df = pd.DataFrame({
    '': list(accuracies.keys()),
    '': [f'{acc:.3f}' for acc in accuracies.values()],
    '': [info[''] for info in models_performance.values()]
})
print(summary_df.to_string(index=False))
print("=" * 80)

# 
best_model = max(accuracies, key=accuracies.get)
print(f'\n: {best_model} (: {accuracies[best_model]:.3f})')
